@node Opening the feed
@section Opening the feed

@findex infovore
The command @code{infovore} is the main entry point.  It opens (or switches @*
to) the @samp{*infovore*} buffer, which displays the curated feed list.  On @*
first invocation it initializes the database and instantiates source @*
objects from @code{infovore-sources}.  Subsequent calls simply switch to the @*
existing buffer and refresh the displayed items. @*

This command does not start the automatic fetch timer.  To begin @*
periodic fetching, call @code{infovore-start} separately @*
(@ref{Starting and stopping}). @*

@node Starting and stopping
@section Starting and stopping

@findex infovore-start
@findex infovore-stop
The command @code{infovore-start} activates the automatic fetch timer.  It @*
instantiates all configured sources, opens the database, and schedules @*
periodic fetch cycles at the interval specified by @*
@code{infovore-fetch-interval} (@ref{Scheduling settings}).  The first fetch cycle @*
runs immediately.  If a timer is already active, it is cancelled and @*
replaced.  A confirmation message is displayed in the echo area. @*

The command @code{infovore-stop} cancels the automatic fetch timer.  It does @*
not close the database or destroy the feed list buffer; it simply stops @*
future fetch cycles from being scheduled. @*

@node Manual fetching
@section Manual fetching

@findex infovore-fetch-now
The command @code{infovore-fetch-now} triggers an immediate fetch cycle @*
outside the normal timer schedule.  If a fetch cycle is already in @*
progress, it displays a message and does nothing.  This is useful for @*
pulling in new content on demand without waiting for the next scheduled @*
cycle.  It is also bound to @samp{G} in the feed list @*
(@ref{Feed list commands}). @*

@node Feed list commands
@section Feed list commands

@findex infovore-list-show-item
@findex infovore-list-browse-url
@findex infovore-list-toggle-read
@findex infovore-list-toggle-starred
@findex infovore-list-refresh
@findex infovore-list-show-all
@findex infovore-list-show-curated
The following commands are available in @code{infovore-list-mode}, the major @*
mode for the @samp{*infovore*} feed list buffer. @*

The command @code{infovore-list-show-item}, bound to @samp{RET}, opens the item at @*
point in the detail view below the feed list @*
(@ref{Item detail commands}).  If no item is at point, it signals an error. @*

The command @code{infovore-list-browse-url}, bound to @samp{b}, opens the original @*
URL of the item at point in the default web browser via @code{browse-url}. @*
If the item has no URL, it signals an error. @*

The command @code{infovore-list-toggle-read}, bound to @samp{r}, toggles the @*
read/unread state of the item at point.  The new state is persisted to @*
the database immediately and the list is refreshed to update the visual @*
styling.  Read items are displayed with @code{infovore-read-face} (inherits @*
from @code{shadow}), making them visually dimmed. @*

The command @code{infovore-list-toggle-starred}, bound to @samp{s}, toggles the @*
starred state of the item at point.  Starred items are displayed with @*
@code{infovore-starred-face} (inherits from @code{warning}, bold).  The state is @*
persisted to the database immediately. @*

The command @code{infovore-list-refresh}, bound to @samp{g}, re-queries the @*
database and repopulates the list.  In the default curated view, it @*
shows only items where @code{curated} is true and @code{score} is at or above @*
@code{infovore-relevance-threshold}.  In the ``show all'' view, it displays @*
every item regardless of curation status. @*

The command @code{infovore-list-show-all}, bound to @samp{+}, switches the feed @*
list to display all items including uncurated ones.  This is useful for @*
reviewing everything that has been fetched. @*

The command @code{infovore-list-show-curated}, bound to @samp{-}, switches back to @*
the default curated view, showing only items that have been scored and @*
meet the relevance threshold. @*

The full keymap for @code{infovore-list-mode}: @*

