@item @samp{p}
@tab @code{previous-line}
@end multitable

@node Refreshing and filtering
@section Refreshing and filtering

@findex infovore-list-refresh
The command @code{infovore-list-refresh} queries the database and rebuilds the @*
feed list.  The query depends on the current view mode: @*

@itemize
@item
In the default curated view, items are filtered to those where @*
@code{curated} is true and @code{score} is at or above @*
@code{infovore-relevance-threshold} (@ref{AI curation settings}). @*
@item
In the ``show all'' view (toggled with @samp{+}), all items are shown. @*
@end itemize

In both cases, items are sorted by timestamp in descending order (newest @*
first).  After refreshing, the item count is displayed in the echo area. @*

@node Item detail commands
@section Item detail commands

@findex infovore-show-item
@findex infovore-show-toggle-view
@findex infovore-show-browse-url
@findex infovore-show-next
@findex infovore-show-prev
The following commands are available in @code{infovore-show-mode}, the major @*
mode for the @samp{*infovore-entry*} detail buffer. @*

The function @code{infovore-show-item} opens an item in the detail view.  It @*
creates or reuses the @samp{*infovore-entry*} buffer, displays it in a @*
window below the current one (occupying 40% of the frame height), and @*
renders the item's summary by default.  The header section shows the @*
title, author, source type, date, score, and a clickable URL@. @*

The command @code{infovore-show-toggle-view}, bound to @samp{TAB} and @samp{t}, @*
toggles between the summary and original content views.  In summary @*
mode, the AI-generated summary is displayed as plain text.  In original @*
mode, the full content is rendered --- HTML content is processed through @*
@samp{shr} for rich display, while plain text is inserted directly. @*

The command @code{infovore-show-browse-url}, bound to @samp{b}, opens the current @*
item's URL in the default web browser. @*

The command @code{infovore-show-next}, bound to @samp{n}, advances point in the @*
feed list window to the next line and displays that item in the detail @*
view.  This allows you to read through items sequentially without @*
switching back to the list buffer. @*

The command @code{infovore-show-prev}, bound to @samp{p}, moves to the previous @*
item in the feed list and displays it. @*

The full keymap for @code{infovore-show-mode}: @*

