@end multitable

@node Mode line indicator
@section Mode line indicator

@findex infovore-mode-line-mode
@findex infovore-modeline-update
The global minor mode @code{infovore-mode-line-mode} adds an indicator to the @*
mode line showing the count of unread curated items.  When enabled, the @*
mode line displays @samp{[IV:N]} where @emph{N} is the number of unread curated @*
items.  When there are unread items, the indicator uses @*
@code{infovore-modeline-active-face} (bold, amber foreground); when the count @*
is zero, it uses the default @code{infovore-modeline-face}. @*

Enable it in your init file: @*

@lisp
(infovore-mode-line-mode 1)
@end lisp

The count is updated automatically after each fetch cycle.  You can also @*
call @code{infovore-modeline-update} manually to refresh the count from the @*
database at any time. @*

